<h5><strong>Musculo Skeletal Health Issues (Carpal tunnel syndrome, Stress Injuries ..) - </strong></h5>
The most commonÂ  are :
1. Upper limb disorders such as Repetitive strain injury (RSI).
2. Tenosynovitis.
3. Carpal tunnel syndrome.
4. Back and neck pain discomfort.
5. Tension stress headaches related ailments. Increases the chances of severity of the existing ailment.
<h6><strong>CausesÂ  -</strong>
- Maintaining an unnatural or unhealthy posture such as inadequate lower back support.<img class="wp-image-201 alignright" src="http://wellnessway4u.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/article-2184618-048EF7A4000005DC-81_468x525-267x300.jpg" alt="Health and safety hazards while using a computer" width="188" height="212" />
- Sitting in same position for an extended period of time.
- An ergonomically poor workstation set up.</h6>
