<h6><strong>Few Precautions</strong>Â to avoid Eye Strain are -
a)Â  Blinking regularly / Exercising the eyes by periodically (20:20) focusing on objects at varying distancesÂ while working on computer continuously.
b)Â  Keeping the air around you moist .For example using plants, open pans of water or a humidifier (spider plants resaid to be particularly good for this and removing chemical vapours from the air.)
c)Â  Adjust the screen and document holder at the same distance from your eyes, screen height/seating so that when sitting comfortably your eyes are in line with the top of the monitor screen. Position monitors to avoid glare.(eg. Not directly in front of windows)
d)Â  Adjust the refresh rate, brightness &amp; contrast control of your monitor to make the characters distinct from the background for comfortable reading.
e)Â  Servicing, repairing or replacing monitor that flicker or have inadequate clarity.</h6>
<h6></h6>
<h6><strong>Regular Eye TestingÂ </strong>-</h6>
Do this at least once every 2 years and more frequently especially if you are experiencing eye problems. Indicate the distance from your eyes to the monitor to your optician and talk to them regarding special lenses or the use of bifocals.

